    "description":  "Information for candidates applying for the Deputy Director Employment Group vacancy in the Government Legal Department based in Leeds",
    "details":  {
                    "attachments":  [

                                    ],
                    "body":  "\u003cdiv class=\"govspeak\"\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"headline-information\"\u003eHeadline Information\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ctable\u003e\n  \u003ctbody\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd\u003eDepartment\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd\u003eGovernment Legal Department\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd\u003eDivision\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd\u003eEmployment Group\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd\u003eJob title\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd\u003eDeputy Director\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd\u003eLocation\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd\u003eLeeds\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd\u003eSalary\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd\u003e\n\u003cabbr title=\"Senior Civil Service\"\u003eSCS\u003c/abbr\u003e Payband 1 - £68,000\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n    \u003ctr\u003e\n      \u003ctd\u003eApplication deadline\u003c/td\u003e\n      \u003ctd\u003eMonday 17 June 2019\u003c/td\u003e\n    \u003c/tr\u003e\n  \u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"vacancy-details\"\u003eVacancy details\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/government-legal-department\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eGovernment Legal Department (\u003cabbr title=\"Government Legal Department\"\u003eGLD\u003c/abbr\u003e)\u003c/a\u003e is the largest provider of legal services across government, working with all the main Whitehall departments. From roads to rivers, and health to human rights, our work touches on most aspects of public life.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe are a non-ministerial government department with more than 2,500 employees, around 1,800 of whom are solicitors or barristers.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Employment Group consists of approximately 90 lawyers who provide employment and litigation services to all government departments. This is an exciting opportunity to manage a busy team and to join \u003cabbr title=\"Government Legal Department\"\u003eGLD\u003c/abbr\u003e in a senior leadership role.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis post is based in Leeds. It involves being joint head of one of the five Employment teams (E4). This particular team is split between Leeds and London. Leadership and management of the team will be shared with another \u003cabbr title=\"Senior Civil Service\"\u003eSCS\u003c/abbr\u003e lawyer based in London.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis particular team also leads on all \u003cabbr title=\"Transfer of Undertakings (Protection of Employment) Regulations\"\u003eTUPE\u003c/abbr\u003e work across government. This means that it is involved in the employment aspects of government contracts, in particular those involving insourcing or outsourcing and works closely with \u003cabbr title=\"Government Legal Department\"\u003eGLD\u003c/abbr\u003e’s Commercial Law Group. A certain amount of litigation and \u003cabbr title=\"Transfer of Undertakings (Protection of Employment) Regulations\"\u003eTUPE\u003c/abbr\u003e work now goes out to external law firms and the relationship with those providers has become an increasingly important part of the role.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eE4’s largest clients are the \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-of-health-and-social-care\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eDepartment of Health and Social Care\u003c/a\u003e (and its associated arm’s length bodies) and the \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-work-pensions\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eDepartment of Work and Pensions.\u003c/a\u003e Other clients include the \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/foreign-commonwealth-office\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eForeign \u0026amp; Commonwealth Office\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.nationalcrimeagency.gov.uk/\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eNational Crime Agency\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/highways-england\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eHighways England.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"apply\"\u003eApply\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv class=\"call-to-action\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.odgersberndtson.com/en-gb/opportunities#AssignDetail.aspx?guid=72366\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eApply for this vacancy\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"contact\"\u003eContact\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor an initial conversation about this role please contact \u003ca href=\"mailto:rhys.keating@odgersberndtson.com\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eRhys Keating\u003c/a\u003e or telephone 0207 529 3949.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003c/div\u003e",
